headline: CVS Health beats quarterly profit expectations on pharmacy performance
summary: Feb 10 () - CVS Health reported a decline in fourth-quarter profit on Tuesday but beat Wall Street estimates, helped by strength in its pharmacy benefit unit and strong prescription ​volume at its retail pharmacies. CVS said adjusted quarterly profit fell to $1.
